§8 — API REST (endpoints, req/resp) [CERRADA]
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

CONVENCIONES GENERALES:

  - Base URL: /api
  - Auth: JWT en header `Authorization: Bearer <token>` excepto en
    /api/auth/* y /api/public/*.
  - Tenant scoping: automático vía TenantScopingMiddleware (extrae
    tenant_id del JWT). Nunca se pasa tenant_id en URL ni en body.
  - Content-Type: application/json (excepto uploads → multipart/form-data).
  - Paginación: ?page=N&page_size=M (default page_size=20, max=100);
    respuesta envuelve `{ items, page, page_size, total }`.
  - IDs: UUIDv7 (ordenados por tiempo, mejores para BD).
  - Errores: JSON `{ error: { code, message, details? } }` + status HTTP.
    Códigos clave: 400 ValidationError, 401 Unauthenticated, 403
    TenantScopeViolation, 404 NotFound, 409 Conflict (KnowledgeBaseInUse,
    IncompatibleEmbeddings), 422 SemanticError (UnsupportedDocumentType,
    SchemaIntrospection), 429 RateLimited, 500 InternalError.
  - Timestamps: ISO-8601 UTC.

CATÁLOGO DE ENDPOINTS POR CAPABILITY:

  CAP-AUTH-IDENTITY
    POST   /api/auth/register
             body  { email, password }
             resp  { user, tenant, token }     (BootstrapTenant ejecutado)
    POST   /api/auth/login
             body  { email, password }
             resp  { user, tenant, token }
    POST   /api/auth/login/google
             body  { google_id_token }
             resp  { user, tenant, token }     (crea cuenta si no existe)
    GET    /api/me
             resp  { user, tenant }
    (Logout es 100% cliente: borra token local. JWT no se revoca server
    side en MVP por sesión corta 1h.)

  CAP-INTEG-CREDENTIALS (+ catálogo lectura)
    GET    /api/providers/llm          → list[LLMProviderDescriptor]
    GET    /api/providers/embedding    → list[EmbeddingProviderDescriptor]
    GET    /api/credentials            → list[ProviderCredentialView]
    POST   /api/credentials
             body  { provider_id, label, api_key, base_url? }
             resp  ProviderCredentialView      (sin api_key)
    DELETE /api/credentials/{id}        → 204
    POST   /api/credentials/{id}/test
             body  { model_id }
             resp  { ok, latency_ms, error? }

  CAP-KB-LIFECYCLE (+ DOC + DB sources)
    GET    /api/knowledge-bases                         → page[KB]
    POST   /api/knowledge-bases
             body  { name, description?, chunking_config,
                     embedding_selection }
             resp  KB
    GET    /api/knowledge-bases/{kb_id}                 → KB + sources[]
    PATCH  /api/knowledge-bases/{kb_id}
             body  partial; si cambia chunking/embedding → 200
                   con `{ kb, reindex_jobs: [IngestionJob] }`
    DELETE /api/knowledge-bases/{kb_id}                 → 204
             409 si referenciada (KnowledgeBaseInUseError).
    GET    /api/knowledge-bases/{kb_id}/sources         → list[Source]
    POST   /api/knowledge-bases/{kb_id}/sources/documents
             multipart upload (file)   OR   body { cloud_folder_ref }
             resp  DocumentSource
    POST   /api/knowledge-bases/{kb_id}/sources/databases
             body  { driver, credential_id, params }
             resp  DatabaseSource
    POST   /api/knowledge-bases/{kb_id}/sources/test-connection
             body  { spec }    (no persiste)
             resp  { ok, error? }
    POST   /api/sources/{source_id}/ingest              → IngestionJob
    POST   /api/sources/{source_id}/reindex             → IngestionJob
    POST   /api/sources/{source_id}/introspect          → SchemaSnapshot
                                                          (síncrono)
    DELETE /api/sources/{source_id}                     → 204
    GET    /api/ingestion-jobs/{job_id}                 → IngestionJob

  CAP-CHATBOT-LIFECYCLE
    GET    /api/chatbots                                → page[ChatbotSummary]
    POST   /api/chatbots
             body  { name, description?, system_prompt, llm_selection,
                     kb_ids: [uuid...], pipeline_config, widget_config }
             resp  Chatbot
             409 IncompatibleEmbeddingsError si las KBs no comparten
                 embedding_selection.
    GET    /api/chatbots/{chatbot_id}                   → Chatbot + kbs[]
    PATCH  /api/chatbots/{chatbot_id}                   → Chatbot
    DELETE /api/chatbots/{chatbot_id}                   → 204
             (cascada sesiones + mensajes; NO toca KBs)

  CAP-CHATBOT-WIDGET-CONFIG
    PATCH  /api/chatbots/{chatbot_id}/widget-config
             body  WidgetConfig (colores, fuentes, avatar, saludo,
                                allowed_domains[])
             resp  Chatbot
    (lectura embebida en GET /api/chatbots/{id})

  CAP-CHAT-AGENT-LOOP (playground autenticado) + CAP-CHAT-SESSIONS
    POST   /api/chatbots/{chatbot_id}/chat
             body  { session_id?, message }
             resp  { session_id,
                     message: { id, role, content, citations[],
                                iterations[] } }
    GET    /api/chatbots/{chatbot_id}/sessions          → page[SessionSummary]
    GET    /api/sessions/{session_id}                   → ChatSession + msgs

  CAP-WIDGET-RUNTIME (público, sin JWT, con CORS)
    GET    /api/public/chatbots/{chatbot_id}/widget-config
             resp  PublicWidgetConfigDTO  (subset no-sensible)
    POST   /api/public/chatbots/{chatbot_id}/chat
             body  { session_id?, message }
             resp  { session_id,
                     message: { id, role, content, citations[] } }
             (sin iterations[] — telemetría no se expone públicamente)
             cookie HttpOnly para session_id si no se pasó.

  CAP-EVAL-RAGAS
    No expone endpoints HTTP. CLI:
      python -m backend.cli eval-ragas \
             --chatbot-id <uuid> --dataset <path> --scenario <name>

SHAPES CLAVE (resumen — el detalle vive en §9):

  LLMSelection         { provider_id, credential_id?, model_id }
                       credential_id sólo para TENANT_CREDENTIAL
  EmbeddingSelection   { provider_id, credential_id?, model_id, dim }
  ChunkingConfig       { strategy: 'fixed'|'by_structure'|'semantic',
                         size, overlap, ... }
  PipelineConfig       { top_k, score_threshold, agentic_mode,
                         max_retrieval_iterations, enable_reranker,
                         reranker_initial_top_k,
                         abstain_when_insufficient,
                         router_llm_selection? }
  WidgetConfig         { colors{primary,bg,text}, font_family,
                         position, avatar_url?, greeting, allowed_domains[] }
  RetrievedChunk       { id, content, source_id, source_type, score,
                         metadata{} }
  RetrievalIteration   { iter_n, tool, args, result_summary, latency_ms }
  IngestionJob         { id, source_id, status:
                         queued|running|done|failed,
                         progress, error?, started_at, finished_at? }

POLÍTICA DE RATE-LIMITING (esbozo, detalle en §12):
  - /api/auth/login y /api/auth/register: 10 req/min/ip.
  - /api/public/chat: 60 req/min/(chatbot_id, ip).
  - Resto: 600 req/min/tenant.

