§9 — Modelo de datos (Postgres + Qdrant) [CERRADA]
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

POSTGRES — esquemas y tablas (PK siempre UUIDv7 `id`; columnas
`created_at`, `updated_at` UTC en todas; FKs ON DELETE según se indica):

  users
    id PK, email UNIQUE, password_hash (bcrypt) NULL si Google-only,
    google_sub UNIQUE NULL, tenant_id FK→tenants.id
    índices: email (UNIQUE), google_sub (UNIQUE), tenant_id

  tenants
    id PK, name, qdrant_collection (TEXT, único físico), storage_prefix,
    created_at

  provider_credentials
    id PK, tenant_id FK→tenants.id ON DELETE CASCADE,
    provider_id (string del catálogo), label, api_key_encrypted (BYTEA),
    base_url NULL, config_source ('SERVER_ENV'|'TENANT_CREDENTIAL')
    índices: (tenant_id, provider_id, label) UNIQUE

  knowledge_bases
    id PK, tenant_id FK→tenants.id ON DELETE CASCADE, name, description,
    chunking_config (JSONB), embedding_selection (JSONB)
    índices: tenant_id, (tenant_id, name) UNIQUE

  sources
    id PK, kb_id FK→knowledge_bases.id ON DELETE CASCADE,
    type ('document'|'database'),
    payload (JSONB)   -- subtipos polimórficos:
                          document: { kind: 'upload'|'cloud',
                                      storage_uri|cloud_folder_ref,
                                      filename, mime_type, size_bytes,
                                      cloud_provider? ('gdrive'|'s3') }
                          database: { driver: 'postgres'|'mysql',
                                      credential_id (cifrado externo),
                                      host, port, db_name, ssl_mode,
                                      schema_snapshot (JSONB) }
    ingest_status ('not_started'|'queued'|'running'|'done'|'failed')
    last_ingest_at NULL,
    error TEXT NULL
    índices: kb_id, (kb_id, type)

  source_db_credentials
    id PK, source_id FK→sources.id ON DELETE CASCADE,
    connection_string_encrypted (BYTEA)
    (separada de provider_credentials para no mezclar dominios)

  chatbots
    id PK, tenant_id FK→tenants.id ON DELETE CASCADE,
    name, description, system_prompt,
    llm_selection (JSONB), router_llm_selection (JSONB NULL),
    pipeline_config (JSONB), widget_config (JSONB)
    índices: tenant_id, (tenant_id, name) UNIQUE

  chatbot_knowledge_base    (tabla N:M)
    chatbot_id FK→chatbots.id ON DELETE CASCADE,
    kb_id FK→knowledge_bases.id ON DELETE RESTRICT (bloquea borrado de
                                                    KB si referenciada),
    PRIMARY KEY (chatbot_id, kb_id)

  chat_sessions
    id PK, chatbot_id FK→chatbots.id ON DELETE CASCADE,
    tenant_id FK→tenants.id (denormalizado para filtrar rápido),
    origin ('playground'|'widget'),
    public_session_cookie NULL (cookie del widget, NULL en playground),
    created_at, last_activity_at
    índices: chatbot_id, public_session_cookie

  chat_messages
    id PK, session_id FK→chat_sessions.id ON DELETE CASCADE,
    role ('user'|'assistant'|'system'),
    content TEXT,
    citations (JSONB)        -- [{ source_id, chunk_id, score }, ...]
    metadata (JSONB)         -- { iterations: RetrievalIteration[] }
    created_at
    índices: (session_id, created_at)

  ingestion_jobs
    id PK, source_id FK→sources.id ON DELETE CASCADE,
    tenant_id (denormalizado), status, progress (int 0-100),
    error TEXT NULL, started_at, finished_at NULL
    índices: source_id, tenant_id

QDRANT — colecciones:

  Una colección física por tenant: `kb_chunks__<tenant_id>`.
  Vector size: variable según embedding (default 1024 para BGE; el
  campo `dim` de EmbeddingSelection lo determina al crear la KB).
  Distance: cosine.

  Payload por punto:
    {
      tenant_id: uuid       (filtro mandatorio en TODO query)
      kb_id: uuid           (filtro por kb_id en search)
      source_id: uuid       (chunk pertenece a un DocumentSource)
      chunk_index: int
      content: string       (texto del chunk)
      metadata: { page_number?, section?, source_filename?, ... }
    }

  Filtros default en search:
    must = [ { key: 'tenant_id', value: <ctx.tenant_id> },
             { key: 'kb_id', values: <chatbot.kb_ids> } ]

INVARIANTES Y CONSTRAINTS DE INTEGRIDAD:

  - Todo SELECT/UPDATE filtra por tenant_id (vía repository pattern;
    repos sólo aceptan ctx con tenant_id).
  - knowledge_bases.embedding_selection JSONB válido con campo `dim` y
    `model_id` requeridos (CHECK constraint).
  - sources.type = 'database' ⇒ payload.driver IN ('postgres','mysql').
  - sources.type = 'document' ⇒ payload.kind IN ('upload','cloud').
  - chatbots.pipeline_config.max_retrieval_iterations IN [1..5].

MIGRACIONES:
  Alembic. Una migración por feature/proposal. Migraciones reversibles.
  Cero migraciones manuales en datos productivos.

